summary: - Squadron Superintendent responsible for all facets of Formal Training Unit operations, responsible for recruiting and staffing for 4 specialty careers within the organization. - Senior intelligence professional with airborne experience in RIVET JOINT, COMPASS CALL and SILENT SHIELD, ground experience with the Afghanistan Remote Operations Cryptologic Center (AROCC) and leadership duties with Project LIBERTY - Heavy focus on education and training as a Command Language Program Manager, RIVET JOINT instructor and evaluator, SILENT SHIELD Cryptologic Skills Program Manager, COMPASS CALL instructor, ACC course manager, Formal Training Unit Superintendent, Defense Language Institute Military Language Instructor and Superintendent of Language Operations - Cryptologic Language Analyst (SIGINT) w/19+ years of experience in training, administrative support, data base creation & management, scheduling, building and presenting intelligence briefings, overall computer application and maintenance proficiency, maintaining operations budgets, developing, coordinating and implementing operational plans - Tactical and strategic level experience in deployed operations as a leader, operator and mission planner during fourteen deployments – 7 x OSW, 2 x ONW, 2 x OIF, 2 x OEF, 1 x OND

description: Provide counsel to the commander in the execution of the EC-130H COMPASS CALL Field Training Unit. Ensure effective use of ACC accredited syllabi for the initial qualification training of 8 Air Force Specialties. Provide input to the commander on personnel, budgetary and other issues as needed. Ensure proper staffing levels and recruit/interview new personnel for placement. Maintain a database of potential future candidates. - Managed $2.5B in training resources and supervised an academic contract worth $6.4M/yr - Directed 81 instructors in the accomplishment of 1.7K training events exceeding 29K hours - Produced 182 qualified aviators, bested historic days late average by 30%, stayed on budget - Farsi and Dari SME, led the development & modification of 22 regionally accredited syllabi - Ensured proper administration of the Command Language Prgm and the Cryptologic Skills Prgm - Guided training and professional development of 150+ cryptologic language analysts

description: - Led the Persian-Farsi School contingent while on assignment to the Curriculum Development Division, coordinated with deans, department chairs, curriculum developers, editors and production coordinators on the first new Persian-Farsi Basic Course curriculum in over 30 years. - Incorporated Merrill, Kolb and Bloom’s principles during the instructional design process, incorporated direct, explicit grammar instruction and tasked based instruction, promoted an eclectic approach to instructional design that promoted maximum creativity, placed special emphasis on personalized and creative activities that teachers can adapt according to students’ different learning styles, developed a degree of automaticity during the achievement stage of learning via repetition, substitution, transformation & expansion – critical to proficiency growth - Developed materials promoting development in both general proficiency and the Performance Final Learning Objectives (FLOs) which focused on Military and Security, Economic and Politics, Science and Technology, Culture and Society and Geography – Physical, Political and Economic. Also incorporated ancillary FLOs which include dictionary use, manner or tenor, colloquial usage, text processing and transliteration according to customer requirements - Developed lesson evaluations in the form of student self-assessments and unit tests, piloted materials, gathered and analyzed data and developed final revision for delivery to end users - During curricula production, involved the users of the products (faculty and students) during various phases of development and production, incorporated interested parties during the initial development, the design of scope and sequence and the design and field testing of the course components including lessons, homework, quizzes, unit test, etc.

summary: - Squadron Superintendent responsible for all facets of Formal Training Unit operations, responsible for recruiting and staffing for 4 specialty careers within the organization. - Senior intelligence professional with airborne experience in RIVET JOINT, COMPASS CALL and SILENT SHIELD, ground experience with the Afghanistan Remote Operations Cryptologic Center (AROCC) and leadership duties with Project LIBERTY - Heavy focus on education and training as a Command Language Program Manager, RIVET JOINT instructor and evaluator, SILENT SHIELD Cryptologic Skills Program Manager, COMPASS CALL instructor, ACC course manager, Formal Training Unit Superintendent, Defense Language Institute Military Language Instructor and Superintendent of Language Operations - Cryptologic Language Analyst (SIGINT) w/19+ years of experience in training, administrative support, data base creation & management, scheduling, building and presenting intelligence briefings, overall computer application and maintenance proficiency, maintaining operations budgets, developing, coordinating and implementing operational plans - Tactical and strategic level experience in deployed operations as a leader, operator and mission planner during fourteen deployments – 7 x OSW, 2 x ONW, 2 x OIF, 2 x OEF, 1 x OND

description: - Chief Military Language Instructor, aided the Dean of the Persian-Farsi School, managed 220+ staff and faculty and 440+ joint-service & coalition students, improved graduation rates 23% - Led 23 AF MLIs as Superintendent of Language Operations, provided instruction in 9 languages at 4 schoolhouses to 3K+ joint-service & coalition students, improved graduation rate by 15% - Represented the Defense Language Institute at the Cryptologic Training Advisory Group, streamlined Farsi course by 15% and accelerated support to overseas contingency operations. - Developed the Persian-Farsi School Mentoring Program, identified and secured mentoring for 63 struggling students, directed 53 tutors in the delivery of 893 academic instruction hours - Managed student load 520% higher than NSA standard, delivered 2340 hours of target language instruction, integrated NSA Final Learning Objectives w/focus on transcription & gisting - Utilized DLI – ICC principles, instructed 520+ hours annually, focused on translation, grammar, listening, reading, speaking and writing, extensive use of blackboard, Elmo, smart board, adobe, foreign language font keyboards/computer software and other language teaching technologies - Evaluated program effectiveness and student performance, provided expertise on military language applications, sourced authentic instructional media and developed testing instruments - Worked w/SMEs to identify what students need to learn, developed objectives and ensured content matched objectives, revised/rewrote content to shape it for learning needs, structured content/activities for student learning, created media to support learning (e.g., visual aids for face-to-face, various multimedia for e-learning and online), developed assessments, adapted materials created for one format to another format (i.e. face-to-face to e-learning)

summary: - Squadron Superintendent responsible for all facets of Formal Training Unit operations, responsible for recruiting and staffing for 4 specialty careers within the organization. - Senior intelligence professional with airborne experience in RIVET JOINT, COMPASS CALL and SILENT SHIELD, ground experience with the Afghanistan Remote Operations Cryptologic Center (AROCC) and leadership duties with Project LIBERTY - Heavy focus on education and training as a Command Language Program Manager, RIVET JOINT instructor and evaluator, SILENT SHIELD Cryptologic Skills Program Manager, COMPASS CALL instructor, ACC course manager, Formal Training Unit Superintendent, Defense Language Institute Military Language Instructor and Superintendent of Language Operations - Cryptologic Language Analyst (SIGINT) w/19+ years of experience in training, administrative support, data base creation & management, scheduling, building and presenting intelligence briefings, overall computer application and maintenance proficiency, maintaining operations budgets, developing, coordinating and implementing operational plans - Tactical and strategic level experience in deployed operations as a leader, operator and mission planner during fourteen deployments – 7 x OSW, 2 x ONW, 2 x OIF, 2 x OEF, 1 x OND

summary: - Squadron Superintendent responsible for all facets of Formal Training Unit operations, responsible for recruiting and staffing for 4 specialty careers within the organization. - Senior intelligence professional with airborne experience in RIVET JOINT, COMPASS CALL and SILENT SHIELD, ground experience with the Afghanistan Remote Operations Cryptologic Center (AROCC) and leadership duties with Project LIBERTY - Heavy focus on education and training as a Command Language Program Manager, RIVET JOINT instructor and evaluator, SILENT SHIELD Cryptologic Skills Program Manager, COMPASS CALL instructor, ACC course manager, Formal Training Unit Superintendent, Defense Language Institute Military Language Instructor and Superintendent of Language Operations - Cryptologic Language Analyst (SIGINT) w/19+ years of experience in training, administrative support, data base creation & management, scheduling, building and presenting intelligence briefings, overall computer application and maintenance proficiency, maintaining operations budgets, developing, coordinating and implementing operational plans - Tactical and strategic level experience in deployed operations as a leader, operator and mission planner during fourteen deployments – 7 x OSW, 2 x ONW, 2 x OIF, 2 x OEF, 1 x OND

summary: I had a career in the medical field with multiple positions of responsibility before retiring to raise my family. I chose to return to the work force and I sought to start a career in law enforcement. I work for the Riverside County Sheriff Public Administrator. My real strength is found in my tenacity and curiosity which drives me to think outside the box to make relationship links between associates and the decedent. After all, in this brave new world of information overload, there's a real need to gather information and make sense of it. Essentially, as an analyst in my position, I must have a keen eye for detail, have an ability to multi-task, think outside the box, and be deadline efficient. It's important work requiring astute analysis of relationships and financial information that builds a platform to make critical decisions and form legal strategies. Additionally, I must effectively communicate with estranged family members as well as the community. My prior experience in the medical field had made this position as investigator/analyst one that emulates my strengths and skills. It definitely tapped into my passions and career decisions to follow my strengths. To that end, I obtained a DOJ Crime and Intelligence Analyst Certificate which required a 400 hr. practicum.

description: As an Estate Investigator, I am responsible for the indigent who die in Riverside County who have no family or those who die that are abandoned by family. In addition, I am responsible to safe guard those assets and personal property that is subject to loss or misappropriation; until such time that family is located or the county takes control as no family could be found. Examples of duties are: I perform searches for Wills and Trusts. I perform internet searches to locate family. I interview friends, neighbors or associates to obtain information that assist in family or asset searches. Internet searches include such programs as Lexus/ Nexis, Accurint, Ancestry, CLETS searches including, NAMS, DRNM(DMV Registrations), search for gun and vehicle registrations, real property title searches and utilizing other internet search sites such as Google, 411.com, and Riverside County Superior Court. I am required to testify in court. I exam legal instruments and provide direction to family who has the right to control said assets. I search the deceased residence for Wills/Trusts and preneeds. I marshall those assets that are deemed subject for loss or misappropriation. Additionally, I inventory the furnishings/property of the decedent, I take photos of the interior of the decedent's homes/assets and perform electronic searches for title/deed, vehicle and gun registrations and stock/bond searches. Finally, I provide detail, concise written reports of all findings.

description: As an SSO for the Coroner's Bureau, I performed support tasks to assist the Deputy Coroner's in their death investigation. Some duties include: picking up admit blood, and hospital medical records. Stocking coroner vehicles with required/necessary supplies, maintain a log of property brought in by deputy coroners and released to appropriate family members. I kept detailed records of weapons used in suicide deaths and destroyed said weapons in accordance to policy. Assisted in the monthly Coroner Review presentation; a summary of findings of officer involved deaths presented to the Sheriff, Administrative Chiefs, and the Grand Jury. In addition, I provided a detail log of vehicle repairs and submitted the monthly mileage of all vehicles. I performed other tasks as necessary and asked upon.

In addition, my department was considered the training model in which new hires from sister facilities would come for training.

description: In the 7 years of employment at Apple Valley Care Center, I held multiple positions of responsibilities. They are as follows: As an admission co-ordinator I was responsible for all admissions into the facility. Such duties included screening the level of care for each patient coming from the acute hospitals. I confirmed insurance coverages and obtained appropriate HMO authorizations. I was promoted to Social Service Designee/Discharge Planner. As a discharge planner, I co-ordinated upward to 60 discharges in a month- primarily in the medicare wing. Some examples of such duties were: to assess safety issues of the discharged patient, set up ancillary support services such as in home support services and I prepared family and patient of their limitiations and insurance coverage. Additionally, I attended skilled care assessment meetings in which patients progress (or lack of) was discussed, discharge goals were established and care plan goals were discussed. I initiated family meetings to problem solve various issues identified during the hospital stay. In addition to discharge planning duties, I was a Social Service Designee. I assessed the residents' social needs and charted personal history and plan of care in the medical chart. I handled complaints and acted as a liaison between departments and family and/or residents in seeking positive solutions. I promoted to Office Manager in which I was responsible for the implementing of business systems in the Medicare and Medi-Cal systems. In addition, I was responsible for accounts receivable billing with a particular attention to the delinquent accounts. As a consequence, I successfully recovered thousands of delinquent monies from all insurances. I ended my employment as Assistant to the Hospital Administrator in which I provided budget assistance and other administrative duties including hiring, firing and training personnel.

summary: I had a career in the medical field with multiple positions of responsibility before retiring to raise my family. I chose to return to the work force and I sought to start a career in law enforcement. I work for the Riverside County Sheriff Public Administrator. My real strength is found in my tenacity and curiosity which drives me to think outside the box to make relationship links between associates and the decedent. After all, in this brave new world of information overload, there's a real need to gather information and make sense of it. Essentially, as an analyst in my position, I must have a keen eye for detail, have an ability to multi-task, think outside the box, and be deadline efficient. It's important work requiring astute analysis of relationships and financial information that builds a platform to make critical decisions and form legal strategies. Additionally, I must effectively communicate with estranged family members as well as the community. My prior experience in the medical field had made this position as investigator/analyst one that emulates my strengths and skills. It definitely tapped into my passions and career decisions to follow my strengths. To that end, I obtained a DOJ Crime and Intelligence Analyst Certificate which required a 400 hr. practicum.

summary: I am proven leader, who works very well in both a structured / regimented environment as well as in a solo capacity. Even as a Project Manager, I retain the ability to remain focused to the “Team Oriented” concept. I am a proven problem solver and I think very well under pressure. Due to my diversity, I possess very strong communication skills, both direct and interpersonal. I have the ability to travel as needed, fitting well into any environment. I understand the difference between Supervision and Management, always leading by example. 27 years of Military experience, both Active Duty as well as Reserve. Career emphasis most recently, has been holding a direct leadership position, serving as the Chief Instructor for the Florida Counterdrug Program, Law Enforcement Training Mission, mentoring junior level instructors, providing quality control on classes, developing new curriculum and providing cutting edge tactical training to Local, State and Federal Law Enforcement Agencies. Currently sworn as a certified Law Enforcement Officer in the State of Florida, serving as the departmental Lead Training Officer, in a part-time capacity. I have served in the past as a Criminal Intelligence Analyst for the Florida Counterdrug Program, and have extensive experience in Counter Threat Financing, Narco-Terrorism Threat Analysis and multiple disciplines within this arena. Proven communicator, proven leader under stress. Military experience centered around the Tactical Signal Intelligence (SIGINT) arena assigned to US Army Special Operations as a Special Operations Team - Alpha (SOT-A) Team Member / Team Sergeant, progressing to Tactical Human Intelligence (HUMINT) / Source Operations. Multiple deployments in both theaters of operations, as well as other areas of interest, working daily in chosen Military Occupational Specialty (MOS).

description: Interrogates and debriefs as defined by regulation, the UCMJ, and other applicable regulations and agreements. Supervises the technical performance of subordinate military and civilian personnel in related job skills. Develops and approves interrogation plans and missions. Advise the support element on the best employment of HUMINT Collector assets. Coordinates closely with other intelligence and non-intelligence agencies of interrogation and MSO. Writes, reviews, and approves interrogation and Intelligence reports and limited technical intelligence reports.

summary: I am proven leader, who works very well in both a structured / regimented environment as well as in a solo capacity. Even as a Project Manager, I retain the ability to remain focused to the “Team Oriented” concept. I am a proven problem solver and I think very well under pressure. Due to my diversity, I possess very strong communication skills, both direct and interpersonal. I have the ability to travel as needed, fitting well into any environment. I understand the difference between Supervision and Management, always leading by example. 27 years of Military experience, both Active Duty as well as Reserve. Career emphasis most recently, has been holding a direct leadership position, serving as the Chief Instructor for the Florida Counterdrug Program, Law Enforcement Training Mission, mentoring junior level instructors, providing quality control on classes, developing new curriculum and providing cutting edge tactical training to Local, State and Federal Law Enforcement Agencies. Currently sworn as a certified Law Enforcement Officer in the State of Florida, serving as the departmental Lead Training Officer, in a part-time capacity. I have served in the past as a Criminal Intelligence Analyst for the Florida Counterdrug Program, and have extensive experience in Counter Threat Financing, Narco-Terrorism Threat Analysis and multiple disciplines within this arena. Proven communicator, proven leader under stress. Military experience centered around the Tactical Signal Intelligence (SIGINT) arena assigned to US Army Special Operations as a Special Operations Team - Alpha (SOT-A) Team Member / Team Sergeant, progressing to Tactical Human Intelligence (HUMINT) / Source Operations. Multiple deployments in both theaters of operations, as well as other areas of interest, working daily in chosen Military Occupational Specialty (MOS).

description: Ranger Proof Consulting has been an outlet for me to showcase certain tactical gear and tactical tools for use in Military and Law Enforcement duty. By using equipment in a "hard use", realistic environment, I am able to see what works and what does not work for specific mission requirements. I do not just evaluate gear based on limited use, I use this gear as it is intended, over a long period of time. If the piece of gear meets my high standards of performance, then I will deem it "Ranger Proof" and be able to recommend the equipment to the end user. Due to my involvement with Local, State and Federal Law Enforcement Agencies, I have the ability to guide individuals as well as departments in gear selection as it fits their needs. By tapping into the Social Media world, I have been able to establish myself as an end user, with knowledge and history, so that when I recommend or endorse a product, the consumer can rest assured that either I have, or those I trust have used it to its limit and found that it does what it advertises. I have partnered with many companies in the firearms / tactical industry, to test and evaluate their product lines in a very hard use setting. Feedback is given, along with Social Media coverage to increase product awareness and branding. The following list are companies that I have done extensive work with: • Primary Weapons Systems (PWS) • CMC Triggers • Alamo Four Star • GPI Manufacturing • Azimuth Technologies • US Optics • Bushnell Elite • War Sport Industries • Odin Works • Stark Equipment • Delta P Design • LeHigh Defense • GemTech • Diamondback Tactical • GreyFox Industries • Skallywag Tactical

description: Served as the 1SG (First Sergeant) for Delta Company (Anti-Armor) of the 1st Battalion, 124th Infantry (Florida Army National Guard). As the Senior NCO (Non Commissioned Officer) I assisted the Company Commander and Executive Officer in direct management and supervision of all service members in the company. I oversaw and carried out all aspects of training, making sure that the company was in a high state of readiness should a deployment or a call up to State Active Duty occur.

description: Chief Law Enforcement Instructor / Program Manager for the Law Enforcement Training Mission for the Florida Counterdrug Program, providing world class, tuition free training to Local, State, and Federal law enforcement agencies. As the Chief Instructor, I would oversee and manage a team of Instructors, mentor the team through instructor development, and ensure that all courses are up to date and relevant. Live fire training (Pistol, Rifle, Shotgun, Precision Rifle) as well as Force on Force scenarios with Simmunition / UTM helps Tactical Teams stay on the cutting edge within their scope of duty. As the Program Manager, I supervised and mentored six full time Law Enforcement Instructors, developed class curriculum and POI, vetted POI and assured quality control. Instructor development was key to my leadership model. Travel and expense sheets were also my responsibility.

summary: I am proven leader, who works very well in both a structured / regimented environment as well as in a solo capacity. Even as a Project Manager, I retain the ability to remain focused to the “Team Oriented” concept. I am a proven problem solver and I think very well under pressure. Due to my diversity, I possess very strong communication skills, both direct and interpersonal. I have the ability to travel as needed, fitting well into any environment. I understand the difference between Supervision and Management, always leading by example. 27 years of Military experience, both Active Duty as well as Reserve. Career emphasis most recently, has been holding a direct leadership position, serving as the Chief Instructor for the Florida Counterdrug Program, Law Enforcement Training Mission, mentoring junior level instructors, providing quality control on classes, developing new curriculum and providing cutting edge tactical training to Local, State and Federal Law Enforcement Agencies. Currently sworn as a certified Law Enforcement Officer in the State of Florida, serving as the departmental Lead Training Officer, in a part-time capacity. I have served in the past as a Criminal Intelligence Analyst for the Florida Counterdrug Program, and have extensive experience in Counter Threat Financing, Narco-Terrorism Threat Analysis and multiple disciplines within this arena. Proven communicator, proven leader under stress. Military experience centered around the Tactical Signal Intelligence (SIGINT) arena assigned to US Army Special Operations as a Special Operations Team - Alpha (SOT-A) Team Member / Team Sergeant, progressing to Tactical Human Intelligence (HUMINT) / Source Operations. Multiple deployments in both theaters of operations, as well as other areas of interest, working daily in chosen Military Occupational Specialty (MOS).

description: I served as the Tactical Human Intelligence (TAC HUMINT) Platoon Sergeant for A Co. 260th Military Intelligence Battalion (Linguist). As the Platoon Sergeant, I was responsible for the training and mentor-ship of the TAC HUMINT Collection Teams (THT's). All personnel issues that had to be taken care of within my platoon were handled by me, and I answered directly to the TAC HUMINT Platoon Leader and the Company First Sergeant. During my tenure as PSG, I deployed twice into combat operations as a Human Intelligence Collector / Arabic Linguist / Interrogator.

summary: I am proven leader, who works very well in both a structured / regimented environment as well as in a solo capacity. Even as a Project Manager, I retain the ability to remain focused to the “Team Oriented” concept. I am a proven problem solver and I think very well under pressure. Due to my diversity, I possess very strong communication skills, both direct and interpersonal. I have the ability to travel as needed, fitting well into any environment. I understand the difference between Supervision and Management, always leading by example. 27 years of Military experience, both Active Duty as well as Reserve. Career emphasis most recently, has been holding a direct leadership position, serving as the Chief Instructor for the Florida Counterdrug Program, Law Enforcement Training Mission, mentoring junior level instructors, providing quality control on classes, developing new curriculum and providing cutting edge tactical training to Local, State and Federal Law Enforcement Agencies. Currently sworn as a certified Law Enforcement Officer in the State of Florida, serving as the departmental Lead Training Officer, in a part-time capacity. I have served in the past as a Criminal Intelligence Analyst for the Florida Counterdrug Program, and have extensive experience in Counter Threat Financing, Narco-Terrorism Threat Analysis and multiple disciplines within this arena. Proven communicator, proven leader under stress. Military experience centered around the Tactical Signal Intelligence (SIGINT) arena assigned to US Army Special Operations as a Special Operations Team - Alpha (SOT-A) Team Member / Team Sergeant, progressing to Tactical Human Intelligence (HUMINT) / Source Operations. Multiple deployments in both theaters of operations, as well as other areas of interest, working daily in chosen Military Occupational Specialty (MOS).

description: As a Senior Level Human Intelligence Collector (HUMINT) I was activated and assigned to the 56th Stryker Brigade Combat Team and deployed to Camp Taji, Iraq. During my attachment to the 2/104th Cavalry, I served as the Operational Management Team Chief (OMT) and supervised four, four-man Human Intelligence Collection Teams. These teams were stationed at Joint Support Sites throughout our operational area. My scope of duty included many areas of influence. I supervised and mentored the junior collectors, aiding and guiding in collection focus, interrogation strategies, questioning plans, and force multipliers to the Combatant Commanders. I also was able to handle Source Operations on and around Camp Taji. My Arabic language capabilities, allowed me to be assigned as additional duties, to the Squadron Commander, and accompany him to Key Leader Engagement Meetings. I worked hand in hand with a Language Assistant, developing questioning strategies, interrogations, and source assessment. My position also required me to manage all contingency fund reports submitted by the Collection Teams, as well as quality control on all field reporting that the Collection Teams submitted.

description: I joined the Florida Counterdrug Program in March of 2001. I was assigned as a Criminal Intelligence Analyst at the South Florida HIDTA (High Intensity Drug Trafficking Area) Intelligence Center in Miramar, FL. My duties included Tactical Photo Line Ups, Financial Background Investigations, Link Analysis, Pen Link Analysis, Surveillance with the host Law Enforcement Agency, and also tenure on the Florida Seaport Inspection Team. During this time, I became certified through the US Merchant Marine Academy as a Deep Water Seaport Inspector, for Threat Vulnerability Assessments, and worked hand in hand with the Florida Department of Law Enforcement (FDLE) in conducting threat assessments on seaports in Florida, post 9-11. During this time, I worked closely with Narco-Terrorism Task Forces to provide direct Counter-Threat Financing Analysis and association matrices.

description: As a Senior Human Intelligence (HUMINT) Collector, I was tasked to the 192nd MP BN on Camp Bondsteel during Kosovo Force (KFOR) Rotation 5B. I was responsible as the Non-Commissioned Officer in Charge (NCOIC) of the Civilian Police (CIVPOL) Liaison to assist with planning, coordination and liaison between the Military Police, Civilian Police, Ground Unit Commanders and the Military Intelligence (HUMINT) Task Force on Camp Bondsteel, Kosovo. I was responsible for information sharing, intelligence oversight for the KFOR (Kosovo Force) and Regional Commanders. Through this assignment, I was able to successfully meld reporting requirements and collection requirements from the Military side, successfully translating and transferring to the Civilian side. Cross talk between the two task forces yeilding impressive results in the overall mission. My attachment to this Joint Law Enforcement Liaison Task Force allowed me freedom of movement to conduct my mission in a permissive environment.

summary: I am proven leader, who works very well in both a structured / regimented environment as well as in a solo capacity. Even as a Project Manager, I retain the ability to remain focused to the “Team Oriented” concept. I am a proven problem solver and I think very well under pressure. Due to my diversity, I possess very strong communication skills, both direct and interpersonal. I have the ability to travel as needed, fitting well into any environment. I understand the difference between Supervision and Management, always leading by example. 27 years of Military experience, both Active Duty as well as Reserve. Career emphasis most recently, has been holding a direct leadership position, serving as the Chief Instructor for the Florida Counterdrug Program, Law Enforcement Training Mission, mentoring junior level instructors, providing quality control on classes, developing new curriculum and providing cutting edge tactical training to Local, State and Federal Law Enforcement Agencies. Currently sworn as a certified Law Enforcement Officer in the State of Florida, serving as the departmental Lead Training Officer, in a part-time capacity. I have served in the past as a Criminal Intelligence Analyst for the Florida Counterdrug Program, and have extensive experience in Counter Threat Financing, Narco-Terrorism Threat Analysis and multiple disciplines within this arena. Proven communicator, proven leader under stress. Military experience centered around the Tactical Signal Intelligence (SIGINT) arena assigned to US Army Special Operations as a Special Operations Team - Alpha (SOT-A) Team Member / Team Sergeant, progressing to Tactical Human Intelligence (HUMINT) / Source Operations. Multiple deployments in both theaters of operations, as well as other areas of interest, working daily in chosen Military Occupational Specialty (MOS).

description: Ranger qualified team Sergeant for a Special Operations Team - Alpha (SOT-A) Voice Intercept Team in the Florida Army National Guard. Military Intelligence rating as well as a Top Secret security clearance was held during this tenure. My duties included, force protection, electronic interception / direction finding, low level voice intercept, cellular phone methodology and intercept techniques, tactical special operations (waterborne, airborne and long range land operations), Advanced Collection Techniques, Geo-Locating, Cellular Exploitation using CELLEBRITE. Responsible for over $800,000 worth of communications equipment and sensitive cryptographic items as well as supervising four other team members. During my tenure, I deployed to Afghanistan with Support Company, 3rd Battalion, 20th Special Forces Group (Airborne) in support of Operation Enduring Freedom and served as a SOT-A Team Sergeant during combat operations. I was directly attached to Task Force 11 early on, then to Operational Detachment - Alpha (ODA) 361 and ODA 362 in a non-permissive, hostile environment to carry out unilateral and joint Signals Intelligence Missions. Proven, effective leader during austere conditions and high tempo environment.

description: • Responsible for resourcing training and operations for a 150 man Mechanized Infantry Company and provided input in the planning process regarding logistics and operations. • Additional duties included Unit Movement Officer, Company Maintenance Officer, and Air Load Planner. • Successfully moved 150 soldiers and over 20 vehicles, valued at over $30 million dollars, across three countries, maintaining 100% accountability and ensuring the unit was rapidly capable of combat operations within one week of arriving at the final destination. • Developed and led a highly successful company intelligence cell facilitating the removal of al Qaeda Foreign Fighters from Mosul's Southeast neighborhoods, providing the Iraqi Government space to establish effective security. • Conceptualized and facilitated the planning and execution of a Battalion size operation to establish the first combined US/Iraqi Combat Out Post (COP) in one of Mosul's most volatile neighborhoods, ultimately stabilizing the area to allow the Iraqi Government to take control unilaterally.

summary: CEO, The Risk Solution Group Crisis Management and Corporate-Counter Intelligence Counter - Corporate Espionage and Intelligence affects all sizes of businesses, corporations, families and individuals. The Canadian Security Intelligence Service (CSIS) reported that corporate espionage costs Canadian corporations billions of dollars per year. The Risk Solution Group is a Canadian-based, First Nations and US Veteran owned corporate-counter intelligence/espionage and crisis management firm. Our clients, both public and private sector, include corporations, governments, financial institutions, insurers, individuals and families. What sets The Risk Solution Group apart from other organizations is that we focus solely on corporate-counter intelligence and related solutions. Further, our staff has real world experience achieved through various professional roles within the International intelligence community. Having said, we have the extensive experience and capabilities to specialize in the collection, analysis and validation of: HUMIT, OSINT, SIGINT, and GEOINT. Our consultants have further experience in Intelligence Management, Intelligence Collection, Collection Management, Fusion Cell Management, Targeting, Counter Insurgency, Criminal Intelligence, Intelligence Analysis, and Intelligence Operations. What differentiates The Risk Solution Group from others, is our firm has a Canadian and International presence with the ability to provide "on the ground analysis", technical support, assessment and reporting in order to provide solutions to a organizations challenges and /or issues. It is our ongoing mandate to provide training, seminars and lectures to an organizations personnel with the goal to assist in the education of corporate espionage and intelligence issues and solutions. Please see our website at www.therisksolutiongroup.net

description: STRONG BEAR TEACHINGS Strong Bear Teachings is dedicated to promoting healing and well-being, in both the Aboriginal and non-Aboriginal communities. Our approach is firmly rooted in the teachings and traditions of our ancestors and Elders. Our vision is to provide training, tools and resources to assist persons and communities dealing with trauma and PTSD - using both Traditional First Nations ways and Western practices. Please visit our website at www.strongbearteachings.ca

description: INSTRUCTOR - Victoria Ambulance Counselling Unit (VACU), Australia. M.A.N.E.R.S Model of Psychological First Aid Dean also has a licensing agreement with Victoria Ambulance to deliver the M.A.N.E.R.S course throughout North America. The M.A.N.E.R.S model is one of the most effective crisis de-escalation tools in use through out the world. This course has been adapted in Canada with an Aboriginal perspective combined with traditional teachings and ceremony.

summary: CEO, The Risk Solution Group Crisis Management and Corporate-Counter Intelligence Counter - Corporate Espionage and Intelligence affects all sizes of businesses, corporations, families and individuals. The Canadian Security Intelligence Service (CSIS) reported that corporate espionage costs Canadian corporations billions of dollars per year. The Risk Solution Group is a Canadian-based, First Nations and US Veteran owned corporate-counter intelligence/espionage and crisis management firm. Our clients, both public and private sector, include corporations, governments, financial institutions, insurers, individuals and families. What sets The Risk Solution Group apart from other organizations is that we focus solely on corporate-counter intelligence and related solutions. Further, our staff has real world experience achieved through various professional roles within the International intelligence community. Having said, we have the extensive experience and capabilities to specialize in the collection, analysis and validation of: HUMIT, OSINT, SIGINT, and GEOINT. Our consultants have further experience in Intelligence Management, Intelligence Collection, Collection Management, Fusion Cell Management, Targeting, Counter Insurgency, Criminal Intelligence, Intelligence Analysis, and Intelligence Operations. What differentiates The Risk Solution Group from others, is our firm has a Canadian and International presence with the ability to provide "on the ground analysis", technical support, assessment and reporting in order to provide solutions to a organizations challenges and /or issues. It is our ongoing mandate to provide training, seminars and lectures to an organizations personnel with the goal to assist in the education of corporate espionage and intelligence issues and solutions. Please see our website at www.therisksolutiongroup.net

summary: CEO, The Risk Solution Group Crisis Management and Corporate-Counter Intelligence Counter - Corporate Espionage and Intelligence affects all sizes of businesses, corporations, families and individuals. The Canadian Security Intelligence Service (CSIS) reported that corporate espionage costs Canadian corporations billions of dollars per year. The Risk Solution Group is a Canadian-based, First Nations and US Veteran owned corporate-counter intelligence/espionage and crisis management firm. Our clients, both public and private sector, include corporations, governments, financial institutions, insurers, individuals and families. What sets The Risk Solution Group apart from other organizations is that we focus solely on corporate-counter intelligence and related solutions. Further, our staff has real world experience achieved through various professional roles within the International intelligence community. Having said, we have the extensive experience and capabilities to specialize in the collection, analysis and validation of: HUMIT, OSINT, SIGINT, and GEOINT. Our consultants have further experience in Intelligence Management, Intelligence Collection, Collection Management, Fusion Cell Management, Targeting, Counter Insurgency, Criminal Intelligence, Intelligence Analysis, and Intelligence Operations. What differentiates The Risk Solution Group from others, is our firm has a Canadian and International presence with the ability to provide "on the ground analysis", technical support, assessment and reporting in order to provide solutions to a organizations challenges and /or issues. It is our ongoing mandate to provide training, seminars and lectures to an organizations personnel with the goal to assist in the education of corporate espionage and intelligence issues and solutions. Please see our website at www.therisksolutiongroup.net

description: Native Canadian Centre of Toronto is a membership-based, charitable organization located in the heart of downtown Toronto in a beautifully renovated heritage building. NCCT offers a wide range of programs and services based on Native cultural traditions and teachings. All are welcome. The Native Canadian Centre of Toronto envisions a healthy urban Aboriginal community by living, learning and celebrating the Aboriginal culture. We do this by honoring our Aboriginal knowledge and traditions, integrating the spirit of youth and elders, and fostering the development of healthy families. With our commitment to self-determination, we will move toward an empowerment of our community through expanding our facilities and providing better services.

summary: Experienced leader with varied operational tours, and a record of success in challenging environments. Demonstrated ability to understand, communicate, and meet key metrics to achieve specific goals in varied operational and business environments. Almost two decades of management expertise, from annual office plans and budgets to multinational engagement programs providing U.S. material and training to partner nations in support of U.S. strategic goals. Results-oriented leader: planning and organizational skills tested in high-pressure, politically sensitive environments often in crisis or combat conditions; postings include Middle East, Asia and throughout Europe. Superb communicator and motivator, creates effective, loyal teams with people from diverse personal, cultural, and educational backgrounds. Resourceful problem solver ideally suited to develop and implement program initiatives, advise management, and independently lead a team to accomplish these goals, maintains strict budgets in dynamic environments. Seek to contribute to, and be a leader in, an organization that provides management services, as well as consulting in the international business fora. Specialties: Operations and program analysis, Political Risk Analysis, Conflict Resolution, and Joint/Inter-agency processes. Speak, read and write fluent Persian/Farsi; basic understanding of Italian, Spanish and Japanese.

summary: Experienced leader with varied operational tours, and a record of success in challenging environments. Demonstrated ability to understand, communicate, and meet key metrics to achieve specific goals in varied operational and business environments. Almost two decades of management expertise, from annual office plans and budgets to multinational engagement programs providing U.S. material and training to partner nations in support of U.S. strategic goals. Results-oriented leader: planning and organizational skills tested in high-pressure, politically sensitive environments often in crisis or combat conditions; postings include Middle East, Asia and throughout Europe. Superb communicator and motivator, creates effective, loyal teams with people from diverse personal, cultural, and educational backgrounds. Resourceful problem solver ideally suited to develop and implement program initiatives, advise management, and independently lead a team to accomplish these goals, maintains strict budgets in dynamic environments. Seek to contribute to, and be a leader in, an organization that provides management services, as well as consulting in the international business fora. Specialties: Operations and program analysis, Political Risk Analysis, Conflict Resolution, and Joint/Inter-agency processes. Speak, read and write fluent Persian/Farsi; basic understanding of Italian, Spanish and Japanese.

summary: Experienced leader with varied operational tours, and a record of success in challenging environments. Demonstrated ability to understand, communicate, and meet key metrics to achieve specific goals in varied operational and business environments. Almost two decades of management expertise, from annual office plans and budgets to multinational engagement programs providing U.S. material and training to partner nations in support of U.S. strategic goals. Results-oriented leader: planning and organizational skills tested in high-pressure, politically sensitive environments often in crisis or combat conditions; postings include Middle East, Asia and throughout Europe. Superb communicator and motivator, creates effective, loyal teams with people from diverse personal, cultural, and educational backgrounds. Resourceful problem solver ideally suited to develop and implement program initiatives, advise management, and independently lead a team to accomplish these goals, maintains strict budgets in dynamic environments. Seek to contribute to, and be a leader in, an organization that provides management services, as well as consulting in the international business fora. Specialties: Operations and program analysis, Political Risk Analysis, Conflict Resolution, and Joint/Inter-agency processes. Speak, read and write fluent Persian/Farsi; basic understanding of Italian, Spanish and Japanese.

summary: Experienced leader with varied operational tours, and a record of success in challenging environments. Demonstrated ability to understand, communicate, and meet key metrics to achieve specific goals in varied operational and business environments. Almost two decades of management expertise, from annual office plans and budgets to multinational engagement programs providing U.S. material and training to partner nations in support of U.S. strategic goals. Results-oriented leader: planning and organizational skills tested in high-pressure, politically sensitive environments often in crisis or combat conditions; postings include Middle East, Asia and throughout Europe. Superb communicator and motivator, creates effective, loyal teams with people from diverse personal, cultural, and educational backgrounds. Resourceful problem solver ideally suited to develop and implement program initiatives, advise management, and independently lead a team to accomplish these goals, maintains strict budgets in dynamic environments. Seek to contribute to, and be a leader in, an organization that provides management services, as well as consulting in the international business fora. Specialties: Operations and program analysis, Political Risk Analysis, Conflict Resolution, and Joint/Inter-agency processes. Speak, read and write fluent Persian/Farsi; basic understanding of Italian, Spanish and Japanese.
